cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method for unsupervised feature learning for 3D point clouds using deep learning. The method involves joint self-reconstruction and half-to-half prediction using RNNs, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on learning global and local geometry, which is relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses variational constraints for shape generation, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL).
